Concord Fabrics Inc said it hasrestructered its long-term debt with an institutional lender.    The company said it extended its debt by borrowing 15 mlndlrs and paying off its existing term loan of 3,100,000 dlrs,resulting in a new debt of 11.9 mln dlrs.    The company said the remaining funds will be used to equipa prooduction facility in Chino, Calif., and provide workingcapital. Reuter&#3;